  <prompt>
    Document the embeddable-launch pattern for the EmailComposer Code Page so other Spaarke Code Pages, PCF controls, or shared library components can launch the composer from their own UI via `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` (or equivalent).

    Per FR-19 Surface 3: "Embeddable launch from other Code Pages / components via `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` — no central work — opportunistic adoption." This task captures the documented pattern so future adopters have a reference.

    Produce `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/040-embeddable-launch.md` containing:
    1. The canonical launch call (`Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` with `pageType: 'webresource'`)
    2. URL parameter encoding examples for each of the 5 modes
    3. Example callers (hypothetical / sample) — how a wizard, a PCF, or a Code Page would invoke it
    4. Notes on `target` (modal vs inline) trade-offs
    5. Return-value handling (the composer's `onSent` / `onClose` callbacks don't natively bubble back to the caller; document workarounds)
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke developer documentation author. Familiar with `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo`, Dataverse web resource URL patterns, and Spaarke's shared library / Code Page integration patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Research note documents the embeddable-launch pattern with concrete code snippets that future adopters (other Code Pages, PCFs, components) can copy-paste. Wave 6 task 085 (`docs/guides/EMAIL-COMPOSER-COMPONENT-GUIDE.md`) lifts this content into the customer-facing developer guide.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-19, Surface 3 is "no central work" — adoption is opportunistic. But the absence of central work doesn't mean absence of pattern documentation. R3 ships the documented pattern so adopters don't reinvent.

      The Code Page's URL contract is already defined by FR-18 and task 032's URL parameter parsing. This task documents how external callers construct the URL and invoke the launch.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/research/040-embeddable-launch.md (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/src/hooks/useUrlParams.ts (REFERENCE — URL schema)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-19 Surface 3">No central code work; documentation-only deliverable</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Code Page handles its own auth; embedded callers don't pass auth tokens</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Launch via `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` (or `openUrl` for non-Dataverse hosts) — no iframe embedding</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Research note is project-internal; Wave 6 task 085 produces customer-facing guide</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No `.claude/` writes in this Wave 2 task</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/src/hooks/useUrlParams.ts (URL schema source)</file>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/EmailComposer/src/types/url.ts (IEmailComposerUrlParams definition)</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo for web resource" location="src/client/webresources/js/ (existing patterns)">
        `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({pageType: 'webresource', webresourceName: 'sprk_emailcomposer', data: encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(params))}, {target: 1|2, width, height, title})`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read FR-19 Surface 3 + task 032's URL parameter schema (`useUrlParams.ts` + `types/url.ts`).</step>
    <step order="2">Document the canonical launch call:
      ```ts
      const launchEmailComposer = (params: IEmailComposerUrlParams) => {
        const data = encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(params));
        return Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo(
          { pageType: 'webresource', webresourceName: 'sprk_emailcomposer', data },
          { target: 2, width: { value: 80, unit: '%' }, height: { value: 90, unit: '%' }, title: 'Email Composer' }
        );
      };
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="3">Document URL parameter examples for each mode:
      - compose (empty): `{mode: 'compose'}`
      - compose with prefill: `{mode: 'compose', to: 'user@org.com', subject: 'Hello'}`
      - compose with association: `{mode: 'compose', associatedTo: {entity: 'sprk_matter', id: 'abc-123'}}`
      - view: `{mode: 'view', id: '<commGuid>'}`
      - reply: `{mode: 'reply', id: '<commGuid>'}`
      - forward: `{mode: 'forward', id: '<commGuid>'}`
      - draft: `{mode: 'draft', id: '<draftGuid>'}`
    </step>
    <step order="4">Document `target` trade-offs:
      - `target: 1` (inline) — replaces current view; full-page experience; harder to return to caller
      - `target: 2` (dialog) — modal overlay; preserves caller context; recommended for embedded launches
    </step>
    <step order="5">Document return-value handling:
      - The Code Page's `onSent`/`onClose` don't propagate to the launcher; pattern is fire-and-forget
      - For callers needing post-send signal: subscribe to `sprk_communication` create event in Dataverse, or poll for new record post-launch
    </step>
    <step order="6">Provide three hypothetical caller examples:
      - Example 1: Wizard step launches composer with prefilled `associatedTo`
      - Example 2: PCF "Email Selected Records" button launches with `to` derived from picked contacts
      - Example 3: Code Page (e.g., DocumentRelationshipViewer) launches with file attachments via `attachmentSources` future extension
    </step>
    <step order="7">Write `notes/research/040-embeddable-launch.md` with all the above content.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 040 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed.</step>
  </steps>

